47045_Aqara_TM1_Nanoleaf_Skylight_JTuohy_0011.jpg 1440w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1800x2700/1920x2880/filters:focal(900x1350:901x1351):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25333466/247045_Aqara_TM1_Nanoleaf_Skylight_JTuohy_0011.jpg 1920w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1800x2700/2048x3072/filters:focal(900x1350:901x1351):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25333466/247045_Aqara_TM1_Nanoleaf_Skylight_JTuohy_0011.jpg 2048w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1800x2700/2400x3600/filters:focal(900x1350:901x1351):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25333466/247045_Aqara_TM1_Nanoleaf_Skylight_JTuohy_0011.jpg 2400w" src="https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1800x2700/2400x3600/filters:focal(900x1350:901x1351):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25333466/247045_Aqara_TM1_Nanoleaf_Skylight_JTuohy_0011.jpg"/></noscript></span></div></div></figure></div></div><div class="duet--media--caption pt-6 font-polysans-mono text-12 font-light leading-130 tracking-1"><figcaption class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup inline text-gray-13 dark:text-gray-e9 [&amp;&gt;a:hover]:text-black [&amp;&gt;a:hover]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;&gt;a:hover]:text-gray-e9 dark:[&amp;&gt;a:hover]:shadow-underline-gray-63 [&amp;&gt;a]:shadow-underline-gray-13 dark:[&amp;&gt;a]:shadow-underline-gray-63"><em>Aqara’s light has a more traditional look but with high-tech features.</em></figcaption></div></div></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph mb-20 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">Aqara’s light also works with <a href="/2020/11/12/21562177/philips-hue-adaptive-lighting-homekit-ios-14-white-and-color-ambiance">Apple’s HomeKit Adaptive lighting</a>, a feature of Apple Home (so iPhone only) that automatically adjusts the white hue of compatible lights throughout the day, going from cool bluish whites in the early morning to warm orangey whites in the evening. (Only the main light responds to adaptive lighting; the ring light doesn’t have tunable white light.) </p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph mb-20 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">The Nanoleaf Skylight doesn’t work with adaptive lighting or even with the Nanoleaf app’s Circadian lighting feature (which is limited to its <a href="/23706841/nanoleaf-essentials-matter-smart-bulbs-review">Essentials range</a>). However, it does have the option of scheduling its various daylight-mimicking scenes, like “Blue Skies” and “Golden Hour,” to create a similar effect to Adaptive Lighting. </p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph mb-20 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">I set schedules in the Nanoleaf app to have these scenes ramp up brightness over an hour to simulate natural light, and this worked well. But it’s not as easy as using HomeKit’s option — where you just select adaptive lighting once, and it adjusts automatically throughout the day. Setting schedules in the Nanoleaf app is fiddly, with the app eating mine several times. The dynamic scenes are also more impactful than regular light bulbs adjusting their hue, and at times, I found them a bit distracting.</p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph mb-20 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white"><strong>Winner: Aqara</strong></p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><h3 class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-heading mb-20 mt-40 font-polysans text-26 font-medium leading-110 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple md:text-30 [&amp;&gt;a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;&gt;a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin [&amp;&gt;a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;&gt;a]:shadow-underline-white">Lighting effects: Nanoleaf dazzles, Aqara falls short</h3></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><div class="duet--article--article-body-component clear-both block w-full md:ml-[-100px] md:w-outdent"><div class="duet--article--image-group-two-up my-40"><div class="sm:flex sm:flex-row"><div class="mb-20 w-full sm:mb-0 sm:mr-20 sm:w-1/2"><div class="transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out"><div class="fixed inset-0 h-[110vh] w-full bg-white transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out z-[-1] cursor-default opacity-0" role="button" aria-label="Close" tabindex="0"></div><div role="button" aria-label="Zoom" tabindex="0" class="visible z-30 w-full origin-center transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out cursor-zoom-in"><div class="relative transition duration-75 ease-in-out p-0"><div class=""><div class=""><span style="box-sizing:border-box;display:block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:ini